This cephalopod inspired robot is a ghoulish spektor that haunts archeotech ruins.

It is a remix of Akewea's Sci-Fi Sphere Drone (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:5266420) and Franklima260's Mini Servo Arm (https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/sci-fi-sphere-drone)

The arms are fully posable with ball & socket joints at the shoulder, elbow, and wrist.

Since the attachment point to the base is pretty small, I've included 4 additional versions of the tentacles with a rod cutout for pinning of the following sizes
- 1mm brass rod (1.1mm hole)
- 1.5mm brass rod (1.6mm hole)
- 0.8mm thin paperclip (0.9mm hole)
- 1.15mm thick paperclip (1.25mm hole)

The original model is a single piece, meant to be printed in resin, but my experience printing vehicles in resin is not the best, so i prefer print them on PLA. With that in mind, i separated some pieces of the model to make it suitable for FDM printers, specially small parts that will probably break when you try to remove supports, then the best is print them apart and glue them after. Refer the pics to look where each piece goes

Weapons and accesories are small and detailed, and were designed to be printed in resin. You can try to print them in FDM of course, but they will lost a lot of detail, specially with the mining laser.

About the Spotter, i choose a more "technological" option instead a guy with binoculars. It makes more sense i think, and it saved me a lot of work :P

IT'S THE LATE 80's, IN SPAAAAACE!

Everyone has mohawks and piercings!
Industrial Metal head anarchists galore!

Here are a few heavy weapons options for your human sized dudes and dudettes, Inspired by classic Necromunda. I give you low tech solutions to deadly problems.

The BRRT Supression Stubber:
All style and zero substance with this over designed chunk of metal, it'll throw roughly bullet shaped things in a roughly straight line. You'll need steroids top deal with kick up though.

Australian Stubber:
The bullets go in ..... UPSIDE DOWN!?
That's right, make gravity your accomplice when you mow down a MF with this retro gravity fed SOB.

Firehazard:
Loaded with homemade fuel that you can dink in a pinch to get your liver upset, the fire hazard is dangerous to everyone, that's cool right? OSHA are nerds!

BAGL (The Ga-chunk):
The Bow Assisted Grenade Launcher or the BAGL (sometimes called the Ga-chunk!) on account of the sound it makes.
Who says you need fancy gas assisted launching mechanisms? Who had the bright idea to try and launch explosives with smaller explosions?
That guy is dead, because those Ideas are hard to execute.

Why go complicated when you can just update a medieval stonebow with modern polymers and alloys.

Possibly the only "stealth" grenade launcher on the market!

Resin would be Ideal, but I've printed the smaller assault rifles I made on FDM and they barely look any more trash than other necromunda weapons! (0.2 nozzle is necessary)
